Different Types of Managements:-
====================================

Package Mnagement:-
----------------------
apt install s/w -y  -----> To install a package
apt update s/w -y ------> To update a package
apt remove s/w -y  ------> To remove a package
apt list all -y ------->  To list all available packages
apt list installed -y ---->  To list all installed packages
apt list available -y ----> To list all available packages
apt search s/w -y -----> To search a specific package
cat /etc/*release  -----> To show the current server flavour
cat /proc/meminfo  -----> To show the memory information
cat /proc/cpuinfo  -----> To show the cpu information


System Management:- 
------------------------
systemctl start <servicename>   ------> To start a sevice
systemctl stop <servicename>    ------>  To stop a service
systemctl restart <servicename> ------>  To restat a service
systemctl enable <servicename>  ------>  To enable a service
systemctl status <sevicename>   ------>  To check the status of a service


Network Management:-
------------------------
netstat                     ------->  To monitor network connections
netstat -l                  ------->  To show the ports that are listening state
netstat -lt                 ------->  To TCP ports that are listening state
netstat -ltn                ------->  To show ports that are listening state for incoming connectios
sudo netstat -ltnp          ------->  To show ports that are listening state for incoming connectios along with process ID  (It requires sudo permission)

